SIMPLE: lustful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lustful
<hw>Lust"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of
lust; excited by lust.</def> <rj><au>Spenser.</au>
<au>Tillotson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Exciting lust; characterized by lust or
sensuality.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ <xex>Lustful</xex> orgies.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Strong; lusty.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧
<xex>Lustful</xex> health.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sackville.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- sensual; fleshly; carnal; inordinate; licentious;
lewd; unchaste; impure; libidinous; lecherous.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Lust"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Lust"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lustic</ent>⟦br⟧
